    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound FD3S Mazda RX-7 featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This unit maintains healthy compression across both rotors, with a recently overhauled vacuum system utilizing high-temp Viton lines to ensure seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos. The chassis remains rigid, benefiting from the original double-wishbone suspension geometry and a Torsen limited-slip differential that provides exceptional power delivery through the corners. Upgraded with a multi-core aluminum radiator to optimize thermal management and a stainless-steel downpipe to reduce backpressure. The 5-speed manual transmission shifts crisply with no synchro grind. A driver-focused example that prioritizes powertrain integrity and kinematic precision.",
